'There was nothing resembling efforts to prevent people walking by from being hit with brick,' he told the station.

Licensing & inspection data shows contractor Griffin Campbell Construction was handing demolition at multiple adjacent properties along the 2100 block of Market Street, including house number 2136, which came crashing down on Wednesday.

All three properties were either owned by or have ties to New York-based STB Investments.

Field said that after some back-and-forth with a city representative, he was notified that an inspector visited the site in question and found no safety violations.

At a press conference Thursday morning, Philadelphia Department of Licenses & Inspections Commissioner Carlton Williams said that 2136 Market Street was not inspected because demolition work had not begun at the time of Field's complaint.

