'Certain people deserve certain things in life, and what she deserved she didn’t get,’ said friend Michael Morgan.

Roseline Coneth, 52, an immigrant from Sierra Leone, worked as a certified nursing assistant, her loved ones told the station, adding that she came to the country to make their lives better.

She was a mother of nine who enjoyed bargain-hunting - a hobby that brought her to the thrift store on Wednesday morning. Her grieving family are now planning to send her body back to her native West Africa for burial.  

So far, no information has been released on the sixth victim, Mary Simpson.

